%sql

--drop table weblogSessions_timestamps
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS weblogSessions_timestamps(client_ip STRING, url STRING, request STRING, timestamp TIMESTAMP, previous_timestamp TIMESTAMP)

%sql
--drop table weblogSessions_timestamps

INSERT INTO weblogSessions_timestamps
    SELECT client,url, request, timestamp,
        LAG(timestamp) OVER (PARTITION BY client ORDER BY timestamp) AS previous_timestamp
      FROM weblogdata

%sql


--Assumption : For this dataset, sessionization by time window rather than navigation. Using default 15 minutes.

--DROP TABLE weblogSessions_sessions
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS weblogSessions_sessions
    SELECT *,( unix_timestamp(timestamp) - unix_timestamp(previous_timestamp)) as time_diff,
        CASE WHEN unix_timestamp(timestamp) - unix_timestamp(previous_timestamp) > (60 * 15) -- using 15mins as session interval
             OR previous_timestamp IS NULL
        THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_new_session
    FROM weblogSessions_timestamps

%sql

--DROP TABLE weblogSessions_ByIds

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS weblogSessions_ByIds
    SELECT *, SUM(is_new_session) OVER (PARTITION BY client_ip ORDER BY timestamp) AS session_id
    FROM weblogSessions_sessions

%sql
cache Table weblogSessions_ByIds
%md Determine the average session time

%sql

--Avg Session time =  Total Session Time / sessions per IP

SELECT 
    SUM(total_session_time_per_ip) AS amount_of_time, 
    SUM(sessions_per_ip) AS num_of_sessions,
    (SUM(total_session_time_per_ip) / SUM(sessions_per_ip)) / 60 AS average_session_time_in_mins
FROM (
    SELECT client_ip, MAX(session_id) AS sessions_per_ip, SUM(session_time) AS total_session_time_per_ip
    FROM (
        SELECT client_ip, session_id, MAX(unix_timestamp(timestamp)) - MIN(unix_timestamp(timestamp)) AS session_time
        FROM weblogSessions_ByIds
        GROUP BY client_ip, session_id 
        ORDER BY client_ip, session_id
    ) grouped_sessions
    GROUP BY client_ip
) average_sessions

    SELECT
        client_ip, session_id, COUNT(url) AS unique_visits,
        COUNT(url) / MAX(session_id) AS unique_visits_per_session
    FROM (
        SELECT DISTINCT client_ip, session_id, url
        FROM weblogSessions_ByIds  
    ) sessions
    GROUP BY client_ip,session_id
    order by client_ip,session_id

Find the most engaged users
ie the IPs with the longest session times

Find the most engaged users
ie the IPs with the longest session times

paragraphs.text:
%sql

select client_ip, (MAX(unix_timestamp(timestamp)) - MIN(unix_timestamp(timestamp))) / 60 AS session_time_in_mins
from weblogSessions_ByIds
group by client_ip, session_id
order by session_time_in_mins desc
limit 10
